    "intro": "Interpretation moves from what the text says to what it means — tracing the author's intent, the original historical-cultural context, and the canonical location of Genesis 33 within the larger story of redemption. The movements below follow the chapter's three-scene argument: the reconciliation (33:1-11), the diplomatic separation (33:12-16), and the settlement and worship (33:17-20). Where Hebrew vocabulary sharpens the meaning, a brief note supplements the main exposition.",
